Package org.biojava.nbio.structure.secstruc

Enum BridgeType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<BridgeType>
      • org.biojava.nbio.structure.secstruc.BridgeType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<BridgeType>
    public enum BridgeType
extends Enum<BridgeType>
    A bridge is formed by two non-overlapping stretches of three residues each (i-1,i,i+1) and (j-1,j,j+1), where i Depending on two basic patterns, a Bridge can be either of type parallel (H bonds in {(i-1,j) and (j,i+1)} OR {(j-1,i) and (i,j-1)}) or antiparallel (H bonds in {(i1,j) and (j,i} OR {(i-1,j+1) and (j-1,i+1)})
    Author:
    Andreas Prlic, Aleix Lafita
